.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINTIME.EQUALS" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainTime.equals \- Temporal.PlainTime.prototype.equals()
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]equals()\f[B]\f[R] method of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R] instances returns \f[CR]true\f[R] if this
time is equivalent in value to another time (in a form convertible by
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime.from()\f[R]), and \f[CR]false\f[R] otherwise.
They are compared by their time values.
It is equivalent to
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime.compare(this, other) === 0\f[R].
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
equals(other)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]other\f[R]
A string, an object, or a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R] instance
representing the other time to compare.
It is converted to a \f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R] object using the same
algorithm as \f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime.from()\f[R].
.SS Return value
\f[CR]true\f[R] if this time is equal to \f[CR]other\f[R] both in their
time value and their calendar, \f[CR]false\f[R] otherwise.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Using equals()
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] time1 = Temporal.PlainTime.from(\(dq12:34:56\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] time2 = Temporal.PlainTime.from({ hour: 12, minute: 34, second: 56 });
console.log(time1.equals(time2)); \f[I]// true\f[R]

\f[B]const\f[R] time3 = Temporal.PlainTime.from(\(dq00:34:56\(dq);
console.log(time1.equals(time3)); \f[I]// false\f[R]
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainTime.compare()\f[R]
